    "The U-notch impact toughness for C gradient samples is 40, 80, 120, 110, 30 J/cm² corresponding to C content of 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9, 1.1 wt% respectively.",
    "The U-notch impact toughness for Mn gradient samples is 115, 105, 100, 115, 115, 35 J/cm² corresponding to Mn content of 24, 26, 28, 30, 32, 34 wt% respectively.",
    "Yield strength increases by 30~40 MPa for every 0.1 wt% increase in C content due to interstitial solid solution strengthening.",
    "κ-phase precipitates during aging when Al > 6.2 wt%, providing significant hardening effect; grain boundary carbide network forms when Al < 6.2 wt%, severely reducing impact toughness.",
    "β-Mn precipitates at grain boundaries after long-term aging at 550 °C when Mn > 31~32 wt%, causing severe embrittlement."
